messages.content:
the table may contain one or more records but a good example of a table format with a few sample records is <!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Game Prices</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        }
        table {
            width: 100%;
            border-collapse: collapse;
        }
        th, td {
            padding: 8px;
            text-align: left;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
        }
        th {
            background-color: #3498db;
            color: white;
        }
        tr:nth-child(even) {
            background-color: #f2f2f2;
        }
        tr:hover {
            background-color: #ddd;
        }
        .separator {
            border-top: 2px solid #3498db;
            margin-top: 20px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
        #link {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<h2>Game Prices</h2>

<p><a id="link" href="#">Product link</a></p>

<p>Date: 2024-04-23</p>

<table>
    <tr>
        <th>Seller Name</th>
        <th>Price</th>
        <th>Seller Rating</th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Seller A</td>
        <td>$0.00</td>
        <td>97%</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Seller B</td>
        <td>$0.00</td>
        <td>94%</td>
    </tr>
 etc....</table>

<div class="separator"></div>

</body>
</html>
